[I] A free Audio Codec optimized for speech

[T] Speex is a patent-free compression format designed especially for speech.
[T] It is specialized for voice communications at low bit-rates in the
[T] 2-45 kbps range. Possible applications include Voice over IP (VoIP),
[T] Internet audio streaming, audio books, and archiving of speech data
[T] (e.g. voice mail).

[U] https://www.speex.org/

